      <preamble>
         <p>The Scottish Ministers make the following Order in exercise of the powers conferred by section 48(2) of the Children and Young People (Scotland) Act 2014<noteRef href="#f00001" class="footnote" marker="1"/> and all other powers enabling them to do so.</p>
         <formula name="enactingText">
            <p>In accordance with section 99(2) of that Act, a draft of this Order has been laid before and approved by resolution of the Scottish Parliament.</p>
         </formula>
      </preamble>
      <body>
         <article eId="article-1">
            <heading>Citation and commencement</heading>
            <num>1.</num>
            <content>
               <p>This Order may be cited as the Children and Young People (Scotland) Act 2014 (Modification) (No. 2) Order 2019 and comes into force on 1 August 2020.</p>
            </content>
         </article>
         <article eId="article-2">
            <heading>Modification of the Children and Young People (Scotland) Act 2014</heading>
            <num>2.</num>
            <paragraph eId="article-2-1">
               <num>(1)</num>
               <content>
                  <p>The Children and Young People (Scotland) Act 2014 is modified in accordance with this article.</p>
               </content>
            </paragraph>
            <paragraph eId="article-2-2">
               <num>(2)</num>
               <content>
                  <p>In section 48 (mandatory amount of early learning and childcare), in subsection (1)(a), for “600 hours” substitute “1140 hours”.</p>
               </content>
            </paragraph>
         </article>
